HEADWORD: Embracery
<hw>Em*bra"cer*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>An attempt to influence a court, jury, etc., corruptly, by
promises, entreaties, money, entertainments, threats, or other improper
inducements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embracive</ent>⟦br⟧
